                                                                  6729 1451
 THERMAL, RESONANCE & UNRESOLVED REGIONS                        &&6729 1451
 Evaluation  by S.F.Mughabghab, March 2006, (BNL)               &&6729 1451
                                                                  6729 1451
 The resolved resonance parameters are adopted from the           6729 1451
 Atlas [Ref. 1]. Only three positive                              6729 1451
 energy resonances below 9 eV are known. Note that the first      6729 1451
 resonance is located at 0.274 eV, close to the cadmium cut-off,  6729 1451
 0.5 eV. The unresolved resonance parameters are derived from     6729 1451
 the systematics described in the Atlas [Ref. 1]. A s-wave        6729 1451
 average level spacing of 4.57 eV is deduced with the aid of      6729 1451
 the Gilbert-Cameron formula and the average level spacing of     6729 1451
 Ho-165.                                                          6729 1451
                                                                  6729 1451
 The average values for the various partial waves  are:           6729 1451
                                                                  6729 1451
 Average  s-wave capture width =  89 meV                          6729 1451
 s-wave   strength function    =  1.95                            6729 1451
                                                                  6729 1451
 Average  p-wave capture width =  45 meV                          6729 1451
 p-wave   strength function    =  1.5                             6729 1451
                                                                  6729 1451
 Average  d-wave capture width = 63 meV                           6729 1451
 d-wave   strength function    = 1.4                              6729 1451
                                                                  6729 1451
 The calculated thermal constants are:                          &&6729 1451
                                                                &&6729 1451
 Capture    =   3600     b                                      &&6729 1451
 Scattering =      3.96  b                                      &&6729 1451
 Total      =   3604     b                                      &&6729 1451
                                                                &&6729 1451
 The calculated capture resonance integral = 676 b  which       &&6729 1451
 includes also contributions from the unresolved region.        &&6729 1451
                                                                &&6729 1451
 The Wescott factor for capture is 1.19613                      &&6729 1451
                                                                  6729 1451
